A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO THE UNIVERSITY OF HAWAII.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that the university of
2 Hawaii system is experiencing sustained enrollment declines,
3 demographic shifts, workforce shortages, and increasing fiscal
4 pressures and this is a matter of statewide concern pursuant to
5 article X, section 6, of the Hawaii State Constitution, that
6 requires careful stewardship of public higher education
7 resources.
8 The legislature further finds that informed institutional
9 planning and rightsizing require transparent, consistent, and
10 comparable data on academic programs, including student demand,
11 completion, cost, and post-graduation outcomes. While the
12 university of Hawaii conducts internal program reviews, the
13 availability and consistency of program-level data across
14 campuses varies and is not readily accessible to students,
15 policymakers, or the public.
16 The legislature also finds that students and their families
17 increasingly require clear, accessible, and comparable
2026-3339 HB2158 GDI HMSO

Page 2
H.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 information to make informed decisions regarding educational
2 pathways, including the total cost of attendance, time to
3 completion, and expected post-graduation outcomes.
4 The purpose of this Act is to improve transparency and data
5 availability primarily to support students and their families in
6 making informed decisions regarding educational pathways and
7 outcomes, while also supporting evidence-based institutional
8 planning, program review, and rightsizing of the university of
9 Hawaii system, and respecting the constitutional authority of
10 the board of regents over internal structure, management, and
11 operation of the university.
12 SECTION 2. Chapter 304A, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
13 amended by adding a new section to part I, subpart A, to be
14 appropriately designated and to read as follows:
15 "§304A- Program level transparency; dashboard; reports.
16 (a) The university of Hawaii shall develop a systemwide data
17 inventory and implementation plan for a publicly accessible
18 online dashboard intended primarily to provide students and
19 their families with clear, comparable, and actionable
20 information regarding academic programs, including cost, time to
21 completion, and post-completion outcomes.
2026-3339 HB2158 CDl HMSO

Page 3
H.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 (b) No later than December 1^ 2026, the university of
2 Hawaii shall submit to the legislature a preliminary report that
3 includes;
4 (1) A comprehensive inventory of existing data elements
5 available across all campuses;
6 (2) Identification of gaps in data collection and data
7 infrastructure;
8 (3) Standardized definitions for key data elements;
9 (4) A phased implementation roadmap for the development of
10 the dashboard, including timelines, methodologies, and
11 priorities; and
12 (5) A proposed list of data elements to be included in the
13 dashboard.
14 (c) Based on the implementation roadmap developed pursuant
15 to subsection (b), the university of Hawaii shall develop,
16 implement, and maintain a publicly accessible, systemwide online
17 dashboard. The dashboard shall be designed with students and
18 their families as the primary audience and shall prioritize
19 clarity, usability, and relevance to decision-making.
