1 (d) The dashboard shall include data elements as
2 determined by the university of Hawaii pursuant to subsection
3 (b)(5)z which may include:
4 (1) Total cost of attendance over time;
5 (2) Median time to degree or completion;
6 (3) Student retention and completion rates;
7 (4) Post-completion outcomes^ including employment status,
8 median earnings, and enrollment in further education;
9 a^
10 (5) Any other information deemed relevant to student
11 decision-making.
12 (e) The university of Hawaii may include additional
13 program-level data elements to support institutional planning
14 and policymaking purposes, including but not limited to cost,
15 capacity, and instructional metrics; provided that the inclusion
16 of such information does not detract from the primary student­
17 facing purpose of the dashboard.
18 (f) All data reported pursuant to this section shall be
19 presented in a manner that protects student privacy and complies
20 with applicable state and federal laws.
