1 (g) No later than December 2027, and annually
2 thereafter, the university of Hawaii shall submit a report to
3 the legislature that includes;
4 (1) Progress on the implementation and operation of the
5 dashboard;
6 (2) Any updates to data definitions or methodologies;
7 (3) Systemwide trends in enrollment, completion, and post­
8 completion outcomes; and
9 (4) How data is being used to inform institutional
10 planning and decision-making, including but not
11 limited to decisions to continue, redesign,
12 consolidate, suspend, or terminate academic programs.
13 (h) The university of Hawaii shall submit a supplementary
14 report to the legislature no later than twenty days prior to the
15 convening of the Regular Session of 2031. The supplementary
16 report shall include findings assessing the relevance,
17 effectiveness, and alignment of the dashboard with its intended
18 purpose, as well as any proposed legislation.
19 (i) The university of Hawaii shall incorporate the data
20 developed pursuant to this section into the board of regents'
